1
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:34,994
You said you gave me

2
00:01:35,028 --> 00:01:36,162
such an expensive gift,

3
00:01:36,296 --> 00:01:37,730
and I didn't prepare anything for you.

4
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:39,732
You did.

5
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:41,935
What?

6
00:01:43,403 --> 00:01:43,970
Long Quan.

7
00:01:44,704 --> 00:01:46,106
Show me a set of Long Fist.

8
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:46,873
Stop!

9
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:50,143
Three against one—

10
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,144
what kind of heroes are you?

11
00:01:51,678 --> 00:01:52,545
Who are you?

12
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,080
Zhang Diao'e.

13
00:01:54,514 --> 00:01:55,482
Remember my name.

14
00:01:55,882 --> 00:01:56,850
Stay out of my way from now on.

15
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:57,450
Get her!

16
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:00,920
That's what you get for bullying people.

17
00:02:09,863 --> 00:02:10,530
Come with me.

18
00:02:17,003 --> 00:02:17,570
Quan.

19
00:02:18,104 --> 00:02:19,672
You don't need to fear those punks.

20
00:02:20,006 --> 00:02:21,174
They're just paper tigers.

21
00:02:21,207 --> 00:02:22,208
One poke and they fall apart.

22
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:23,243
Really?

23
00:02:23,943 --> 00:02:24,878
I'd be a dog if I lied.

24
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:27,413
Besides,

25
00:02:27,747 --> 00:02:29,249
you've got me protecting you.

26
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:30,450
From now on,

27
00:02:30,517 --> 00:02:31,718
if they bully you again,

28
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:33,052
just shout my name:

29
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:34,387
Zhang Diao'e.

30
00:02:35,288 --> 00:02:35,688
Okay.

31
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:36,789
If I ever run into trouble,

32
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:38,358
I'll shout Zhang Diao'e.

33
00:02:43,096 --> 00:02:44,430
That was the gift

34
00:02:44,464 --> 00:02:45,732
you gave me back then.

35
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:48,168
Good thing I found it today.

36
00:02:49,202 --> 00:02:50,203
I'm thinking of changing my name

37
00:02:50,203 --> 00:02:50,970
back too.

38
00:02:52,205 --> 00:02:53,873
I've been Long Jiaojiao for so many years,

39
00:02:55,441 --> 00:02:56,042
but I still think

40
00:02:56,042 --> 00:02:57,110
I'm happier as Long Quan.

41
00:02:58,811 --> 00:02:59,312
Diao'e.

42
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:01,447
Thank you.

43
00:03:06,653 --> 00:03:07,587
Let's live well.

44
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:11,224
We won't depend on anyone.

45
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:40,653
I checked.

46
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,157
Beyond the mountains and the sea

47
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:45,158
isn't far at all.

48
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:47,360
A plane ticket will take us there.

49
00:03:49,095 --> 00:03:50,263
Look. A plane.

50
00:03:50,363 --> 00:03:50,763
Look.

51
00:03:50,830 --> 00:03:51,397
It really is.

52
00:03:52,365 --> 00:03:53,833
Do you think the people on the plane

53
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:55,001
can hear us talking?

54
00:03:56,302 --> 00:03:57,904
Hello!

55
00:03:59,772 --> 00:04:00,907
Hello!

56
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:03,309
Hello!

57
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,748
Are plane tickets expensive?

58
00:04:09,515 --> 00:04:10,883
I'll use miles to get yours.

59
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:13,052
I'm going too?

60
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,087
Of course.

61
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,025
Then we'll fly together.

62
00:04:19,792 --> 00:04:20,493
Together.

63
00:04:25,331 --> 00:04:26,799
How many people can a plane hold?

64
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,035
At least

65
00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:30,169
a few hundred, right?

66
00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:32,105
I've never been on one.

67
00:04:32,405 --> 00:04:33,706
Neither have I.

68
00:04:33,906 --> 00:04:35,575
I'd really love to.

69
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:36,943
We'll definitely fly together someday.

70
00:04:37,243 --> 00:04:37,644
Okay.

71
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:39,512
I'll go to Beijing.

72
00:04:39,679 --> 00:04:41,080
Then I'll go to Shanghai.

73
00:04:41,681 --> 00:04:43,182
And I want to visit Hangzhou.

74
00:04:43,516 --> 00:04:44,984
I want to go to Sanya too.

75
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:45,918
To see the ocean.

76
00:04:46,486 --> 00:04:47,954
Then I'll go to Inner Mongolia

77
00:04:48,054 --> 00:04:48,921
to see the grasslands.

78
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:51,958
Director Kong from the ER just called.

79
00:04:52,358 --> 00:04:53,559
Three patients from lower-level hospitals

80
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:54,427
were transferred here

81
00:04:54,594 --> 00:04:55,695
and want to be admitted.

82
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:56,929
But you turned them down.

83
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:00,733
Are we out of beds?

84
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:02,201
We do have beds.

85
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:03,503
But

86
00:05:05,571 --> 00:05:06,839
all three are critically ill.

87
00:05:07,407 --> 00:05:08,241
I assessed them.

88
00:05:08,307 --> 00:05:09,709
They may not meet

89
00:05:09,842 --> 00:05:10,677
surgical criteria.

90
00:05:10,843 --> 00:05:11,844
And their families only want

91
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:12,645
conservative treatment.

92
00:05:13,546 --> 00:05:14,247
Patients like that

93
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,281
are predictably

94
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,383
likely to occupy beds long-term.

95
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,187
Director.

96
00:05:21,688 --> 00:05:22,755
Since Zhang Diao'e's case

97
00:05:22,955 --> 00:05:24,557
and the rollout of your support policy,

98
00:05:25,024 --> 00:05:26,526
we really have seen

99
00:05:26,526 --> 00:05:27,427
more and more patients

100
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:28,594
transferred from lower-level hospitals.

101
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,163
But

102
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,131
many of them incur high costs,

103
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:33,366
stay a long time,

104
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:34,600
and have poor outcomes.

105
00:05:35,134 --> 00:05:36,436
It only adds

106
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:37,970
more pressure to the department.

107
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:40,173
Our performance pay

108
00:05:40,206 --> 00:05:41,107
had finally improved

109
00:05:41,107 --> 00:05:42,041
a little.

110
00:05:47,914 --> 00:05:49,015
Those hospitals trust us.

111
00:05:49,716 --> 00:05:51,050
We can't cherry-pick patients.

112
00:05:58,624 --> 00:05:59,192
Director Kong.

113
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:00,426
Director Zhou.

114
00:06:00,827 --> 00:06:01,627
A family member is here.

115
00:06:01,894 --> 00:06:02,595
He says he knows you

116
00:06:02,795 --> 00:06:04,330
and insists on seeing you. His surname is Niu.

117
00:06:04,831 --> 00:06:05,932
He's from Jinxi Town, Fuze County.

118
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,734
All right. I'll go now.

119
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:10,870
No more treatment.

120
00:06:12,405 --> 00:06:13,806
Take me home.

121
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:15,208
Sis.

122
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,343
We've come all the way to a major hospital.

123
00:06:17,477 --> 00:06:18,644
We should listen to the doctors.

124
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:20,446
Don't worry.

125
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:22,014
Director Zhou, over here.

126
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:25,151
Director Zhou is here.

127
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,321
Director Zhou.

128
00:06:28,788 --> 00:06:29,722
You're finally here.

129
00:06:30,256 --> 00:06:31,090
I'm Old Niu.

130
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:32,358
Do you remember me?

131
00:06:34,193 --> 00:06:36,162
Last time you held a free clinic in our village,

132
00:06:36,529 --> 00:06:37,830
when Hanxuan's family was poisoned,

133
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,599
I was helping at the clinic too.

134
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:43,503
This is my sister.

135
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,638
Her heart disease is very serious,

136
00:06:45,838 --> 00:06:47,073
and she's severely anemic.

137
00:06:47,373 --> 00:06:48,508
The county hospital said

138
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,309
there was nothing more they could do

139
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,211
and told us to try a major hospital.

140
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,281
Besides her heart problem,

141
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,016
she previously had a gastrointestinal tumor

142
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,451
and now has GI bleeding.

143
00:06:58,684 --> 00:06:59,585
She can't even undergo angiography.

144
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:02,555
My sister raised me from childhood.

145
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:04,524
I need to care for her to the end.

146
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:05,892
I thought

147
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:07,960
if a good director like you

148
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:09,762
also says

149
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,430
there's no treatment left,

150
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,198
then I'll take her home

151
00:07:12,965 --> 00:07:14,233
to the old house

152
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,067
where we grew up.

153
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:17,270
Our parents' memorial tablets

154
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:20,273
are still there.

155
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:24,944
Director Zhou,

156
00:07:25,545 --> 00:07:26,412
please help us.

157
00:07:27,246 --> 00:07:28,414
We came all this way

158
00:07:28,481 --> 00:07:29,715
from the village.

159
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:46,999
Admit all of them.

160
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:48,468
These two to the ward.

161
00:07:48,534 --> 00:07:48,835
Thank you.

162
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:49,969
The elderly woman goes to the ICU.

163
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:50,436
Thank you.

164
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:51,237
Thank you.

165
00:07:51,704 --> 00:07:53,239
Thank you, Director Zhou.

166
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,173
Thank you.

167
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:56,843
Thank you so much, Director Zhou.

168
00:08:04,851 --> 00:08:05,351
All right.

169
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:06,886
It's only a few patients.

170
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,454
No need to look so dejected.

171
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:10,056
I'm just worried.

172
00:08:10,389 --> 00:08:11,190
Our department's performance pay

173
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:12,191
will drop again.

174
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:14,227
What else can we do?

175
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:15,394
We're their

176
00:08:15,394 --> 00:08:16,362
last hope.

177
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:18,731
And with active treatment,

178
00:08:18,865 --> 00:08:19,866
they may recover faster

179
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,067
and transfer out sooner.

180
00:08:21,734 --> 00:08:22,535
Don't be so pessimistic.

181
00:08:22,768 --> 00:08:23,736
But you know, Director,

182
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:25,037
the president has been watching us.

183
00:08:25,271 --> 00:08:26,305
Everyone in the department office...

184
00:08:27,607 --> 00:08:28,074
Hello?

185
00:08:30,643 --> 00:08:31,210
Understood.

186
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:41,988
Everyone,

187
00:08:42,488 --> 00:08:42,989
this month,

188
00:08:42,989 --> 00:08:44,524
both departments

189
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:45,958
in our center have done very well.

190
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:48,394
Cardiology's livestreamed

191
00:08:48,427 --> 00:08:49,195
pulmonary AV fistula intervention

192
00:08:49,562 --> 00:08:50,630
was a great success

193
00:08:51,063 --> 00:08:52,632
and made a major impact in the field.

194
00:08:53,566 --> 00:08:54,600
And Director Zhou's

195
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,735
support program for primary hospitals

196
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:57,803
has also earned excellent feedback.

197
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:00,039
That deserves praise.

198
00:09:07,747 --> 00:09:08,514
Congratulations, Director Zhou.

199
00:09:09,515 --> 00:09:10,583
Everyone else should keep working hard.

200
00:09:10,917 --> 00:09:12,718
Learn from our Cardiology colleagues.

201
00:09:13,319 --> 00:09:14,153
You're too kind, Director Sheng.

202
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,121
We learn from each other.

203
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:18,724
Cardiac Surgery performed brilliantly too.

204
00:09:20,026 --> 00:09:20,793
The success of the transapical

205
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:21,294
transcatheter aortic valve replacement

206
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:22,194
procedure

207
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:23,195
also made a major impact

208
00:09:23,496 --> 00:09:25,031
in the field.

209
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:26,999
The promotion and publicity were excellent too.

210
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,467
Many colleagues in the field

211
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:29,068
have said

212
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:30,770
they want to come learn from us.

213
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:33,773
And the valve program's case volume

214
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,074
has also increased.

215
00:09:35,775 --> 00:09:36,909
That deserves praise too.

216
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:44,650
Also, I heard

217
00:09:44,884 --> 00:09:45,851
one of our

218
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,054
young residents

219
00:09:48,387 --> 00:09:49,388
received an NSFC

220
00:09:49,488 --> 00:09:50,523
Young Scientists Fund grant.

221
00:09:51,223 --> 00:09:51,757
Who was it?

222
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:53,826
Xiao Du.

223
00:09:54,193 --> 00:09:54,594
I'm here.

224
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,762
An outstanding young man.

225
00:09:57,196 --> 00:09:57,863
Your name is...

226
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:58,631
Du Wenzheng.

227
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,166
Du Wenzheng.

228
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:02,168
It seems our center

229
00:10:02,201 --> 00:10:03,369
has a strong next generation.

230
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:04,503
Thank you, President.

231
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:05,371
Sit, sit.

232
00:10:06,072 --> 00:10:06,772
One more thing

233
00:10:06,806 --> 00:10:07,707
to announce.

234
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:09,642
After democratic recommendation,

235
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:11,310
the Party committee has decided

236
00:10:12,144 --> 00:10:13,112
to award this year's

237
00:10:13,245 --> 00:10:14,814
Outstanding Physician title

238
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:15,748
to

239
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:17,917
Fang Xiaoran

240
00:10:18,684 --> 00:10:19,385
from the general ICU.

241
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:21,721
Wonderful.

242
00:10:28,494 --> 00:10:29,128
Thank you, President.

243
00:10:29,362 --> 00:10:29,929
Congratulations.

244
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:30,429
Thank you.

245
00:10:38,104 --> 00:10:39,839
Dr. Fang received

246
00:10:39,872 --> 00:10:40,840
strong support across the entire Heart Center.

247
00:10:41,107 --> 00:10:41,807
And

248
00:10:41,874 --> 00:10:42,875
she works across

249
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,043
two departments,

250
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:46,045
with both her brother and boyfriend

251
00:10:46,045 --> 00:10:47,079
as strong backing.

252
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,081
So the Outstanding Physician title

253
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,282
is, Dr. Fang,

254
00:10:50,516 --> 00:10:51,250
well deserved.

255
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:52,385
Congratulations to you too.

256
00:10:57,523 --> 00:10:59,959
We recommend talent regardless of family ties.

257
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:00,993
Xiao Lin,

258
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,995
you'll need to work harder.

259
00:11:03,529 --> 00:11:03,829
All right.

260
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:06,065
I'll learn from Dr. Fang.

261
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,035
Then first,

262
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,403
find a way to pass

263
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:12,171
the democratic evaluation.

264
00:11:12,204 --> 00:11:12,805
Oh my God.

265
00:11:12,805 --> 00:11:13,806
That's way too hard for him.

266
00:11:16,442 --> 00:11:16,876
All right.

267
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:18,611
If there are no other questions,

268
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:20,680
let's hand over.

269
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,890
Outstanding Physician is worth celebrating.

270
00:11:31,757 --> 00:11:32,725
We have to celebrate

271
00:11:32,758 --> 00:11:33,392
properly.

272
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:34,093
My treat.

273
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:34,960
Let's really mark the occasion.

274
00:11:35,227 --> 00:11:36,962
Wow, you're actually treating.

275
00:11:37,129 --> 00:11:38,230
It really is worth celebrating.

276
00:11:43,969 --> 00:11:45,204
The Outstanding Physician

277
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:46,639
chosen from the whole Heart Center

278
00:11:46,672 --> 00:11:47,440
only comes once a year.

279
00:11:47,907 --> 00:11:49,075
That's impressive.

280
00:11:49,308 --> 00:11:49,809
Exactly.

281
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:51,744
You've never won it, have you?

282
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:52,611
No, no, no.

283
00:11:52,611 --> 00:11:53,279
I haven't.

284
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,081
And you have no idea—

285
00:11:55,414 --> 00:11:56,949
when I attend conferences,

286
00:11:57,316 --> 00:11:58,584
people always ask me

287
00:11:58,717 --> 00:11:59,852
about our Heart Center's

288
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:00,786
operating model.

289
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:02,788
They say the biggest obstacle

290
00:12:02,855 --> 00:12:03,589
is

291
00:12:03,622 --> 00:12:05,224
combining two departments,

292
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:06,792
because no one knows how to manage the ICU.

293
00:12:06,959 --> 00:12:08,360
Who can cover both sides?

294
00:12:08,761 --> 00:12:09,228
That's why

295
00:12:09,328 --> 00:12:10,329
you need someone like Xiaoran,

296
00:12:10,329 --> 00:12:11,397
a core talent

297
00:12:11,797 --> 00:12:13,365
who can connect both departments.

298
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:14,233
You have no idea

299
00:12:14,266 --> 00:12:15,034
how jealous they are.

300
00:12:20,439 --> 00:12:21,874
Not just inside the hospital.

301
00:12:22,475 --> 00:12:24,043
When I went to Fushan Hospital,

302
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,045
the moment I arrived, they kept asking

303
00:12:26,212 --> 00:12:27,046
about Dongli Hospital's

304
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:28,013
general ICU,

305
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:28,881
and Dr. Fang.

306
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:30,282
Everyone wanted to learn from her.

307
00:12:30,616 --> 00:12:31,484
They should.

308
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:32,752
Absolutely.

309
00:12:33,786 --> 00:12:35,354
You have no idea—when I got there,

310
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:36,322
they didn't even know

311
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:37,156
I was Director Lin.

312
00:12:37,356 --> 00:12:38,357
Do you know what they called me?

313
00:12:38,357 --> 00:12:38,758
Do you?

314
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:39,558
What?

315
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:42,294
Dr. Fang's boyfriend.

316
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,331
You should feel some pressure too.

317
00:12:45,397 --> 00:12:46,565
Otherwise, you won't be Director Zhou anymore.

318
00:12:46,632 --> 00:12:47,466
What will I be?

319
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:49,969
Dr. Fang's brother.

320
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:53,873
No wonder you're Outstanding Physician.

321
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:55,074
You even know how to steal the answer.

322
00:12:55,374 --> 00:12:55,975
All right.

323
00:12:56,008 --> 00:12:57,476
That's enough from both of you.

324
00:12:58,043 --> 00:12:59,078
I understand.

325
00:12:59,645 --> 00:13:00,713
No matter what they say,

326
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,881
I know

327
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,282
who I am.

328
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,351
You don't need to worry about me.

329
00:13:08,687 --> 00:13:09,688
Are you really treating?

330
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:12,124
I...

331
00:13:13,159 --> 00:13:13,926
Do I really have to?

332
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,195
Dr. Fang is treating.

333
00:13:16,428 --> 00:13:17,363
Use your meal card.

334
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:20,833
Brother, are you free this weekend?

335
00:13:22,768 --> 00:13:24,370
Ouyang Da's patient club

336
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:25,604
is holding an event.

337
00:13:25,671 --> 00:13:26,906
They've invited a genetics expert

338
00:13:26,906 --> 00:13:27,640
for a discussion.

339
00:13:27,673 --> 00:13:28,874
There'll also be booths,

340
00:13:28,874 --> 00:13:29,875
camping, and so on.

341
00:13:30,409 --> 00:13:31,310
Come with us.

342
00:13:31,610 --> 00:13:32,745
You haven't joined

343
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:33,445
one of our family days

344
00:13:33,445 --> 00:13:34,647
since coming back.

345
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:37,449
Okay.

346
00:13:38,450 --> 00:13:38,918
Fine.

347
00:13:38,951 --> 00:13:40,119
I'll think carefully about

348
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:40,953
the dress code.

349
00:13:42,955 --> 00:13:43,989
What dress code?

350
00:13:44,723 --> 00:13:46,292
Dress code means what to wear.

351
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:47,092
I know.

352
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:48,561
What kind of dress code?

353
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:49,995
What's the theme?

354
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:51,130
The theme is...

355
00:13:51,363 --> 00:13:52,431
Whatever Xiaorui says.

356
00:13:53,465 --> 00:13:54,200
How are you doing?

357
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:55,201
I'm almost done.

358
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:56,268
Right away.

359
00:13:56,435 --> 00:13:57,436
I'll grab some more food.

360
00:13:59,805 --> 00:14:01,607
I can sit in a normal chair.

361
00:14:02,074 --> 00:14:03,609
I don't want this wheelchair.

362
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:06,145
Who said it's for you?

363
00:14:07,479 --> 00:14:08,814
Scenic areas have wheelchair

364
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:09,481
priority lanes.

365
00:14:09,481 --> 00:14:10,783
When we get there, I'll sit and you push me.

366
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:11,116
Okay?

367
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:11,917
It'll save time.

368
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:13,085
Come on, slowly.

369
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,695
Don't move. I'll do it.

370
00:14:27,466 --> 00:14:28,601
What is this?

371
00:14:28,834 --> 00:14:29,735
It's so ugly.

372
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:30,970
A surgical knot.

373
00:14:31,237 --> 00:14:32,438
So your laces won't keep coming undone.

374
00:14:32,571 --> 00:14:33,505
Done. We can go.

375
00:14:33,672 --> 00:14:35,007
Brother said he's already downstairs.

376
00:14:37,610 --> 00:14:38,077
All right.

377
00:14:39,011 --> 00:14:39,845
Here, give it to me.

378
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:40,646
Sister Xiaoran,

379
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:42,214
look what he did to my shoes.

380
00:14:43,015 --> 00:14:43,883
It's so ugly.

381
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:45,985
Why can't surgeons

382
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:47,052
tie a bow

383
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:47,953
during surgery?

384
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,156
You're young but so fussy.

385
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:52,358
A grown man

386
00:14:52,491 --> 00:14:53,559
likes bows?

387
00:14:56,795 --> 00:14:57,162
Brother.

388
00:14:58,964 --> 00:14:59,431
Brother Feng.

389
00:15:02,001 --> 00:15:02,835
That's a lot.

390
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:04,069
It's all his.

391
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:05,771
Months of hard work

392
00:15:06,005 --> 00:15:06,672
are in these boxes.

393
00:15:07,106 --> 00:15:08,374
We'll make a fortune today.

394
00:15:08,674 --> 00:15:09,174
I'll help you.

395
00:15:09,842 --> 00:15:10,943
Stop. You'll clear out my stock.

396
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:18,117
Don't.

397
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,552
That's more like it.

398
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:21,153
Look.

399
00:15:22,521 --> 00:15:23,856
Peace and joy.

400
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,025
Designed by Xiaorui himself.

401
00:15:26,525 --> 00:15:27,426
Let's take a photo.

402
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:28,294
Okay. Come on.

403
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,495
Stand in order.

404
00:15:30,663 --> 00:15:31,330
Departure photo.

405
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:33,365
Show it.

406
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:34,600
All visible.

407
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:36,335
Three, two, one.

408
00:15:36,969 --> 00:15:38,971
Peace and joy!

409
00:15:40,873 --> 00:15:41,307
Done.

410
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:43,108
Let's go.

411
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:46,078
Is this angle okay?

412
00:15:46,245 --> 00:15:46,845
Higher.

413
00:15:48,881 --> 00:15:49,682
Farther back.

414
00:15:51,717 --> 00:15:52,584
Hello, Xiaozhi.

415
00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:54,720
Navigate to the campsite.

416
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:55,354
Okay.

417
00:15:55,921 --> 00:15:58,357
Navigating to the campsite.

418
00:15:59,024 --> 00:15:59,758
Let's go.

419
00:16:11,203 --> 00:16:12,304
How does it feel?

420
00:16:17,509 --> 00:16:18,077
Hello.

421
00:16:18,544 --> 00:16:19,345
Peace and joy.

422
00:16:20,212 --> 00:16:22,047
Wasn't there a dress code?

423
00:16:22,881 --> 00:16:23,849
There was.

424
00:16:23,849 --> 00:16:24,783
We thought it'd be fun.

425
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:26,318
Didn't expect everyone to dress so properly.

426
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,319
So elegant.

427
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:28,120
Right?

428
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,022
And you insisted Xiaorui design it.

429
00:16:30,255 --> 00:16:31,824
That was your idea, wasn't it?

430
00:16:33,225 --> 00:16:34,126
It's not bad.

431
00:16:34,226 --> 00:16:35,527
We're a team, at least.

432
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:38,230
No, I want this one.

433
00:16:40,532 --> 00:16:41,633
But they said...

434
00:16:42,768 --> 00:16:43,335
They're here.

435
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:47,573
Peace and joy.

436
00:16:48,407 --> 00:16:49,108
The meaning is great.

437
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:52,111
The booth is ready. Come over.

438
00:16:52,878 --> 00:16:54,046
Go, go.

439
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:54,513
Let's go.

440
00:16:58,450 --> 00:16:59,051
It's a little cold.

441
00:17:00,886 --> 00:17:02,121
Forest, say hello.

442
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,271
This resin-art collection

443
00:17:19,304 --> 00:17:20,706
is called Frozen Time.

444
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,241
Every petal

445
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:22,975
and leaf inside

446
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:24,443
was grown

447
00:17:24,476 --> 00:17:25,310
by our boss Xiaorui

448
00:17:25,310 --> 00:17:26,645
and carefully selected.

449
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:28,347
This piece combines

450
00:17:28,614 --> 00:17:29,948
rosemary and phalaenopsis orchids.

451
00:17:30,582 --> 00:17:31,483
It's called Endless Butterfly.

452
00:17:34,686 --> 00:17:36,822
I brought a small seedling.

453
00:17:38,123 --> 00:17:38,791
Can I use it

454
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:39,992
to trade for Endless Butterfly?

455
00:17:40,325 --> 00:17:41,493
Is this lady's tresses orchid?

456
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:42,694
Yes.

457
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:45,230
It's very rare

458
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:46,432
and hard to keep alive,

459
00:17:46,765 --> 00:17:47,866
let alone bloom.

460
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:48,967
You've grown it beautifully.

461
00:17:49,368 --> 00:17:50,235
You know it too?

462
00:17:50,436 --> 00:17:51,503
Then I'll feel safe

463
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:52,404
trading it to you.

464
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:53,472
Okay.

465
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:55,007
Pick one.

466
00:17:58,410 --> 00:17:59,311
Then I'll take this one.

467
00:18:00,212 --> 00:18:01,079
Sure.

468
00:18:01,213 --> 00:18:01,647
Thank you.

469
00:18:03,282 --> 00:18:03,949
Boss Forest,

470
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:05,918
Little Garden wants a squirrel.

471
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:06,552
Introduce one to him.

472
00:18:06,685 --> 00:18:07,853
This is lady's tresses, right?

473
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:08,187
Yes.

474
00:18:08,187 --> 00:18:08,687
Lady's tresses.

475
00:18:08,687 --> 00:18:09,488
Then I recommend

476
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:10,789
this little red-bellied squirrel.

477
00:18:10,789 --> 00:18:11,156
Okay.

478
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:12,558
It's called a red-bellied squirrel.

479
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,593
I've seen one in a garden before.

480
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:19,131
Is this okay?

481
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:20,532
Thank you.

482
00:18:23,368 --> 00:18:23,802
Bye.

483
00:18:23,869 --> 00:18:24,903
Bye, Little Garden.

484
00:18:25,804 --> 00:18:26,872
Thirsty? Have some water.

485
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:28,207
I'm not thirsty right now.

486
00:18:28,707 --> 00:18:29,608
The atmosphere is nice.

487
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:31,276
Yeah.

488
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:32,945
We originally just wanted

489
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:33,812
to get Xiaorui out more.

490
00:18:34,012 --> 00:18:35,280
But after coming once,

491
00:18:35,514 --> 00:18:36,281
he really liked it.

492
00:18:37,149 --> 00:18:37,583
All right.

493
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:42,955
One, two, three.

494
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:45,023
How's that?

495
00:18:45,824 --> 00:18:47,092
How can anyone eat it cut like this?

496
00:18:47,426 --> 00:18:48,193
It's not for eating.

497
00:18:48,694 --> 00:18:49,928
It's a hat for Little Forest.

498
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:51,964
Nice craftsmanship.

499
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:53,866
I won't say anything else,

500
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,000
but as for technique—

501
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,401
you know Director An

502
00:18:56,401 --> 00:18:56,935
at Fushan Hospital?

503
00:18:56,935 --> 00:18:57,402
After I did a few

504
00:18:57,402 --> 00:18:57,903
transcatheter aortic valve replacements,

505
00:18:57,903 --> 00:18:58,303
she said I'd already

506
00:18:58,303 --> 00:18:59,238
surpassed the teacher.

507
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:00,305
Yes.

508
00:19:00,672 --> 00:19:01,440
Director Lin's technique

509
00:19:01,507 --> 00:19:02,407
and learning ability

510
00:19:02,441 --> 00:19:03,509
are obvious to everyone.

511
00:19:04,042 --> 00:19:05,677
You should feel some pressure.

512
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:07,513
Given time,

513
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:09,648
the two of us may be evenly matched.

514
00:19:12,351 --> 00:19:13,252
You know what everyone

515
00:19:13,252 --> 00:19:14,119
at the Heart Center says?

516
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:16,188
You're Cardiac Surgery's nuclear weapon.

517
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,890
If Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery

518
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:18,624
ever compete,

519
00:19:18,891 --> 00:19:19,825
you'll eventually be aimed at me.

520
00:19:22,194 --> 00:19:23,228
A nuclear weapon?

521
00:19:28,734 --> 00:19:29,134
Here.

522
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:31,637
What's this?

523
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:33,906
A nuclear weapon needs a switch.

524
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:38,844
I'm giving you the switch.

525
00:19:41,413 --> 00:19:41,880
Press it.

526
00:19:48,453 --> 00:19:49,721
How childish.

527
00:19:53,158 --> 00:19:53,992
Directors.

528
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,595
The genetics expert

529
00:19:56,595 --> 00:19:57,362
you invited, Professor Zhang, has arrived.

530
00:19:57,496 --> 00:19:58,564
Let me introduce you.

531
00:19:58,864 --> 00:19:59,231
All right.

532
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:00,933
Professor Zhang.

533
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:02,868
Professor Zhang.

534
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:14,046
I see you've already used

535
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,081
the latest symptomatic treatments,

536
00:20:17,282 --> 00:20:18,717
implanted a CRT-D,

537
00:20:19,985 --> 00:20:21,386
considered heart transplantation,

538
00:20:22,454 --> 00:20:24,156
and even tried stem-cell therapy.

539
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:25,757
Yes.

540
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,528
You've covered everything thoroughly.

541
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:31,530
But I still don't feel at ease.

542
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:32,931
I want to do something more.

543
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:34,733
When you have time, bring your nephew

544
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,635
to my clinic for testing.

545
00:20:36,935 --> 00:20:38,036
All right. Thank you.

546
00:20:39,771 --> 00:20:40,405
Professor Zhang.

547
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:41,673
Isn't gene-editing technology

548
00:20:41,673 --> 00:20:43,508
quite a hot topic now?

549
00:20:44,309 --> 00:20:44,743
It is.

550
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:46,912
It's being actively explored.

551
00:20:48,146 --> 00:20:49,281
If we can identify

552
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:50,716
the pathogenic gene

553
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:52,317
and mutation site

554
00:20:52,551 --> 00:20:53,785
for his cardiomyopathy,

555
00:20:53,785 --> 00:20:54,720
couldn't we use some form

556
00:20:55,053 --> 00:20:56,655
of delivery system

557
00:20:56,788 --> 00:20:57,990
to precisely target myocardial cells,

558
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,224
deliver the gene-editing tool

559
00:20:59,524 --> 00:21:00,959
into the cells,

560
00:21:01,226 --> 00:21:01,994
rewrite the gene

561
00:21:02,794 --> 00:21:04,229
and cure the disease?

562
00:21:05,163 --> 00:21:06,431
Your thinking is correct.

563
00:21:06,732 --> 00:21:07,432
But at present,

564
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:08,233
the tool is still limited

565
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,668
by the size

566
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:11,837
of the gene fragment it can carry,

567
00:21:11,837 --> 00:21:12,304
the patient's pre-existing neutralizing

568
00:21:12,704 --> 00:21:13,705
antibodies,

569
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,074
and many other factors.

570
00:21:16,174 --> 00:21:17,442
So its clinical application

571
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:19,311
is still restricted.

572
00:21:19,645 --> 00:21:20,445
So

573
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,546
the bottleneck is

574
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:26,718
the delivery tool.

575
00:21:26,718 --> 00:21:27,853
But researchers around the world

576
00:21:27,886 --> 00:21:28,720
are already working hard on it.

577
00:21:28,987 --> 00:21:29,721
Professor Zhang.

578
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:30,889
So perhaps

579
00:21:30,989 --> 00:21:32,090
one day,

580
00:21:32,157 --> 00:21:33,025
cardiomyopathy

581
00:21:33,358 --> 00:21:34,726
may only require one injection.

582
00:21:35,027 --> 00:21:35,827
One injection for a cure.

583
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:38,730
It's entirely possible.

584
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,799
But I'm already retired.

585
00:21:40,999 --> 00:21:42,534
It'll depend on you young people.

586
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:45,003
I really hope that day comes soon.

587
00:21:45,237 --> 00:21:46,471
Then they won't have to

588
00:21:46,471 --> 00:21:47,873
fear even a common cold.

589
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,474
Have faith.

590
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:51,309
The future is in your hands.

591
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:54,079
Please move to the west-side stage.

592
00:21:55,113 --> 00:21:56,214
Xiaorui is about to go on.

593
00:21:58,083 --> 00:21:58,750
Hello.

594
00:21:58,784 --> 00:21:59,985
The first person

595
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:00,719
sharing his story

596
00:22:00,719 --> 00:22:01,386
with us today

597
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,554
is the face

598
00:22:02,554 --> 00:22:03,322
of our club,

599
00:22:03,488 --> 00:22:04,022
Lin Xirui.

600
00:22:04,189 --> 00:22:05,524
Let's welcome him with applause.

601
00:22:11,863 --> 00:22:14,032
Hello, everyone. I'm Lin Xirui.

602
00:22:14,199 --> 00:22:15,067
I'm almost twenty.

603
00:22:15,434 --> 00:22:17,169
I was diagnosed with dilated cardiomyopathy three years ago.

604
00:22:17,235 --> 00:22:18,003
And now,

605
00:22:18,103 --> 00:22:19,771
I've just been upgraded

606
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:20,906
into a low-budget

607
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:23,275
Iron Man.

608
00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:25,110
Iron Man!

609
00:22:26,645 --> 00:22:28,046
Actually, my transformation

610
00:22:28,146 --> 00:22:28,914
was pretty different

611
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:30,115
from the real Iron Man's.

612
00:22:30,549 --> 00:22:31,650
He paid out of pocket.

613
00:22:32,250 --> 00:22:33,952
The CRT pacemaker in my chest

614
00:22:34,286 --> 00:22:35,087
was covered by insurance.

615
00:22:36,955 --> 00:22:37,589
But

616
00:22:37,823 --> 00:22:38,623
Ever since I had

617
00:22:38,623 --> 00:22:39,624
this CRT pacemaker implanted,

618
00:22:39,958 --> 00:22:41,426
whenever I see a pretty girl,

619
00:22:41,727 --> 00:22:42,794
I have to walk the other way.

620
00:22:43,729 --> 00:22:44,730
Because if my heart skips a beat,

621
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:46,565
I literally get shocked.

622
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,267
The dog spoke.

623
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:50,802
I wasn't talking about you.

624
00:22:50,936 --> 00:22:51,570
Don't take it personally.

625
00:22:54,806 --> 00:22:55,807
Luckily, our Eryi

626
00:22:56,441 --> 00:22:57,342
keeps encouraging me.

627
00:22:57,809 --> 00:22:58,543
He says

628
00:22:58,543 --> 00:22:59,911
every flap of a butterfly's wings

629
00:23:00,312 --> 00:23:01,880
can stir up

630
00:23:02,147 --> 00:23:02,914
a whirlwind of love.

631
00:23:03,915 --> 00:23:05,083
But

632
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:05,917
today he tied my shoelaces

633
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:07,586
with a surgical knot.

634
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,721
It was unbelievably ugly.

635
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,323
He can't even tie a bow.

636
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:13,358
How am I supposed to flap my butterfly wings?

637
00:23:33,812 --> 00:23:34,146
Director.

638
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:35,647
Those three patients from Fuze County

639
00:23:35,847 --> 00:23:36,481
stayed

640
00:23:36,481 --> 00:23:37,682
for more than three weeks in total.

641
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:39,050
The last one

642
00:23:39,451 --> 00:23:40,685
was finally discharged today.

643
00:23:41,553 --> 00:23:43,054
Their recovery looked pretty good.

644
00:23:43,255 --> 00:23:44,089
It was.

645
00:23:44,556 --> 00:23:46,091
But Old Niu's family still owes money.

646
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:47,492
They said

647
00:23:47,826 --> 00:23:49,161
they genuinely can't afford it.

648
00:23:49,294 --> 00:23:50,128
They even left

649
00:23:50,162 --> 00:23:50,829
their insurance card as collateral.

650
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:53,799
At least their attitude was sincere.

651
00:23:54,132 --> 00:23:55,066
They said once they have money,

652
00:23:55,233 --> 00:23:56,668
they'll definitely bring it over.

653
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:58,770
Before leaving,

654
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:00,372
they gave the doctors' office

655
00:24:00,605 --> 00:24:02,174
this whole bag of peanuts.

656
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:03,208
Try some.

657
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,412
You can still smile?

658
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:08,947
Our performance pay

659
00:24:09,214 --> 00:24:10,849
will definitely be the worst again this month.

660
00:24:12,984 --> 00:24:14,352
You can't only look at the present.

661
00:24:15,353 --> 00:24:16,354
If we all work hard,

662
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:17,956
treat patients sincerely,

663
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:19,124
and build a good reputation,

664
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:20,091
then in the long run,

665
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:21,693
our performance will improve.

666
00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:31,069
There's a European summit before New Year's.

667
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:31,770
You know about it, right?

668
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:34,406
You should go.

669
00:24:35,874 --> 00:24:36,608
Seriously?

670
00:24:39,744 --> 00:24:41,346
You're giving me such a valuable slot?

671
00:24:41,446 --> 00:24:42,247
Haven't you always wanted

672
00:24:42,247 --> 00:24:43,048
this opportunity?

673
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:45,150
Represent Dongli Cardiology

674
00:24:45,250 --> 00:24:46,284
and exchange ideas with everyone.

675
00:24:46,785 --> 00:24:48,286
What about you? Are you going?

676
00:24:49,187 --> 00:24:50,355
There's too much going on in the department.

677
00:24:50,555 --> 00:24:51,690
I probably can't.

678
00:24:52,157 --> 00:24:52,824
You go.

679
00:24:53,225 --> 00:24:54,292
And relax a little while you're there.

680
00:24:55,193 --> 00:24:55,894
Thank you, Director.

681
00:24:57,796 --> 00:24:58,997
You're the most handsome director.

682
00:25:00,765 --> 00:25:02,868
Your aura is three meters tall today.

683
00:25:03,068 --> 00:25:05,003
Here, everything in my pocket is yours.

684
00:25:06,304 --> 00:25:06,838
Director.

685
00:25:06,872 --> 00:25:07,973
Then I'll go apply for the visa.

686
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:11,276
I'll get back to work.

687
00:25:11,943 --> 00:25:12,544
Thank you, Director.

688
00:25:21,753 --> 00:25:22,287
Pull.

689
00:25:23,722 --> 00:25:24,256
Stroke.

690
00:25:32,597 --> 00:25:33,198
You're here so early.

691
00:25:34,232 --> 00:25:34,799
Didn't go home?

692
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,167
I worked until two last night

693
00:25:36,234 --> 00:25:37,402
and slept in the on-call room.

694
00:25:38,436 --> 00:25:39,571
That dedicated?

695
00:25:41,239 --> 00:25:42,207
For today's surgery,

696
00:25:42,407 --> 00:25:43,775
I'm going to stand tall no matter what.

697
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:48,914
Today is

698
00:25:48,914 --> 00:25:49,848
my hundredth operation with him.

699
00:25:50,749 --> 00:25:51,650
I have a small goal.

700
00:25:53,251 --> 00:25:54,319
I have to make Director Lin

701
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:55,253
see me in a new light.

702
00:25:55,487 --> 00:25:56,154
I must earn

703
00:25:56,154 --> 00:25:57,088
his first word of praise.

704
00:25:57,589 --> 00:25:58,023
Du Wenzheng.

705
00:25:58,323 --> 00:25:58,823
You can do it.

706
00:25:59,157 --> 00:25:59,591
Go for it.

707
00:26:43,034 --> 00:26:43,835
What are you doing?

708
00:26:50,175 --> 00:26:50,842
I'm asking you.

709
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:52,143
Suctioning.

710
00:26:58,083 --> 00:26:59,050
Is he suctioning correctly?

711
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:02,387
No.

712
00:27:03,254 --> 00:27:04,022
I didn't say that.

713
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:05,590
Your classmate did.

714
00:27:07,993 --> 00:27:09,928
We didn't attend the same school.

715
00:27:12,430 --> 00:27:13,064
No wonder.

716
00:27:14,766 --> 00:27:15,767
Your position is right,

717
00:27:16,468 --> 00:27:17,635
but you're blocking the surgeon's view.

718
00:27:17,635 --> 00:27:18,303
Switch hands.

719
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,008
Forget switching hands.

720
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:24,509
Let's switch people.

721
00:27:27,145 --> 00:27:27,645
Then...

722
00:27:27,812 --> 00:27:28,847
Director, I'll call Xiao Zhu.

723
00:27:31,449 --> 00:27:31,916
Director.

724
00:27:32,651 --> 00:27:33,785
Give me one more chance.

725
00:27:35,053 --> 00:27:36,321
I won't let you down.

726
00:27:36,921 --> 00:27:37,956
Just one more chance.

727
00:27:38,523 --> 00:27:39,891
How many surgeries have you followed?

728
00:27:40,759 --> 00:27:41,359
One hundred.

729
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:42,961
That means I've already given you

730
00:27:42,961 --> 00:27:43,828
one hundred chances.

731
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:44,929
Do you think I'm stupid enough

732
00:27:44,929 --> 00:27:45,964
to give you number 101?

733
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:52,570
Suctioning is so simple.

734
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:53,304
Anyone can do it.

735
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:55,073
Can you suction?

736
00:27:58,710 --> 00:27:59,144
Yes.

737
00:28:01,012 --> 00:28:02,013
Can you do it better than him?

738
00:28:06,284 --> 00:28:06,951
I'll try.

739
00:28:07,552 --> 00:28:09,354
Fine. You do it.

740
00:28:09,654 --> 00:28:10,155
Director.

741
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:12,424
Can't understand Mandarin?

742
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:24,436
I really don't know how

743
00:28:24,436 --> 00:28:25,370
you graduated from medical school

744
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:26,438
and even got into a PhD program.

745
00:28:26,704 --> 00:28:27,806
I got in on my own merit.

746
00:28:27,806 --> 00:28:28,707
You got a problem with that?

747
00:28:28,973 --> 00:28:30,575
Were you born knowing how to operate?

748
00:28:30,742 --> 00:28:32,010
Have you ever seriously taught me?

749
00:28:32,243 --> 00:28:33,711
Fine. You're the greatest.

750
00:28:33,912 --> 00:28:35,246
The best in the world.

751
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:36,514
I'm stupid. I'm dumb.

752
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:37,515
I'm a stupid donkey.

753
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:38,349
Happy now?

754
00:28:39,784 --> 00:28:40,318
Switch.

755
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:55,800
What did he just call himself?

756
00:28:55,934 --> 00:28:56,468
A donkey.

757
00:28:57,135 --> 00:28:57,869
And he called you a bull.

758
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:02,073
Xiao Du works very hard.

759
00:29:02,073 --> 00:29:03,074
And he's warm-hearted.

760
00:29:03,475 --> 00:29:04,642
Our patients

761
00:29:04,642 --> 00:29:05,643
all like him.

762
00:29:06,511 --> 00:29:07,278
What do they like about him?

763
00:29:07,612 --> 00:29:08,012
That he's dumb?

764
00:29:10,548 --> 00:29:11,282
Everyone

765
00:29:11,282 --> 00:29:12,884
is good at different things.

766
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:13,885
When he follows surgeries to learn,

767
00:29:13,885 --> 00:29:15,353
you should give him more time.

768
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:16,321
How much?

769
00:29:16,688 --> 00:29:18,423
Three years, five, or ten?

770
00:29:18,890 --> 00:29:20,391
Even if he can afford to learn that long, I can't.

771
00:29:21,326 --> 00:29:22,527
I'm not as tolerant as you.

772
00:29:23,161 --> 00:29:23,895
Then can you

773
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:25,130
learn from me a little,

774
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:25,797
Director Lin?

775
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:27,465
Fine.

776
00:29:28,566 --> 00:29:29,634
Since at least

777
00:29:29,634 --> 00:29:30,769
he showed some backbone today,

778
00:29:31,803 --> 00:29:32,504
give him

779
00:29:32,504 --> 00:29:33,271
my practice kit tomorrow.

780
00:29:33,638 --> 00:29:34,973
We'll see what he's made of.

781
00:29:35,406 --> 00:29:36,374
You're always

782
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:37,842
hard on the outside, soft on the inside.

783
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:40,345
What are you folding?

784
00:29:40,345 --> 00:29:41,412
It's a mess.

785
00:29:42,413 --> 00:29:43,448
This doesn't look anything like

786
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:44,449
the livestream.

787
00:29:44,482 --> 00:29:45,150
In the livestream,

788
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:46,451
he folded it in seconds.

789
00:29:50,054 --> 00:29:50,688
Lin Yi.

790
00:29:51,489 --> 00:29:53,124
You mixed the laundry again.

791
00:29:53,925 --> 00:29:54,793
The colors bled.

792
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:55,760
How am I supposed to wear this next time?

793
00:29:56,394 --> 00:29:57,195
Why wear it again?

794
00:29:57,495 --> 00:29:58,630
After how embarrassing

795
00:29:58,663 --> 00:29:59,864
that last dress-code event was,

796
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:01,466
I doubt he'll ever

797
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,167
wear it again.

798
00:30:04,669 --> 00:30:05,036
By the way,

799
00:30:05,570 --> 00:30:06,571
don't forget to switch shifts

800
00:30:06,571 --> 00:30:07,639
for family day next week.

801
00:30:08,039 --> 00:30:09,407
Xiaorui keeps talking about it.

802
00:30:09,707 --> 00:30:10,875
Bring the pot of lady's tresses

803
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:12,143
we brought back from camping.

804
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:13,545
Don't worry.

805
00:30:14,612 --> 00:30:15,480
I won't forget

806
00:30:16,114 --> 00:30:16,881
my brother's birthday.

807
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:21,853
No need.

808
00:30:22,253 --> 00:30:22,954
You get what you pay for.

809
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:26,124
Stupid donkey.

810
00:30:27,225 --> 00:30:29,093
You're pretty harsh on yourself.

811
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,695
I was angry.

812
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:32,664
Don't all young doctors

813
00:30:32,864 --> 00:30:33,832
go through this?

814
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:34,799
Who hasn't been yelled at by their mentor

815
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,668
for a few years?

816
00:30:37,001 --> 00:30:38,203
Everyone is equal.

817
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:39,871
Even my parents never talked to me like that.

818
00:30:39,971 --> 00:30:40,705
You think the whole world

819
00:30:40,705 --> 00:30:41,806
is your parents?

820
00:30:42,974 --> 00:30:44,843
On your first day, you said

821
00:30:45,310 --> 00:30:47,111
Director Lin was your idol.

822
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:48,513
What now? Unfollowing and turning anti-fan?

823
00:30:48,713 --> 00:30:50,215
I wouldn't go that far.

824
00:30:52,283 --> 00:30:53,251
I wouldn't go that far.

825
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:55,486
Maybe from die-hard fan

826
00:30:56,254 --> 00:30:56,955
to casual fan.

827
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:00,158
Honestly, I acted impulsively.

828
00:31:00,491 --> 00:31:01,326
The moment I left the OR,

829
00:31:01,359 --> 00:31:02,160
I regretted it.

830
00:31:03,161 --> 00:31:04,996
But I really don't understand you.

831
00:31:05,597 --> 00:31:07,398
Do you truly think clinical skills

832
00:31:07,398 --> 00:31:08,800
are harder than an NSFC grant?

833
00:31:09,067 --> 00:31:10,468
They are hard.

834
00:31:10,635 --> 00:31:11,469
Sometimes your eyes understand,

835
00:31:11,469 --> 00:31:12,170
but your hands don't.

836
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:13,404
Then when your hands finally learn,

837
00:31:13,471 --> 00:31:14,305
Director Lin glares at you

838
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,039
and you forget everything.

839
00:31:15,273 --> 00:31:16,374
Your mind goes completely blank.

840
00:31:16,841 --> 00:31:18,076
You should secretly be thrilled.

841
00:31:18,676 --> 00:31:20,712
These days, research drives promotion.

842
00:31:20,912 --> 00:31:21,946
You have a Young Scientists Fund grant

843
00:31:21,946 --> 00:31:23,448
and high-impact papers.

844
00:31:23,648 --> 00:31:24,916
Once you've put in enough years,

845
00:31:25,683 --> 00:31:26,718
you'll rise quickly.

846
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:29,320
I haven't thought that far ahead.

847
00:31:29,787 --> 00:31:30,588
Then let me ask you:

848
00:31:31,322 --> 00:31:32,824
if you're clearly better at research,

849
00:31:33,024 --> 00:31:34,325
why not stay in a lab

850
00:31:34,325 --> 00:31:35,293
as a researcher?

851
00:31:35,693 --> 00:31:37,128
Why insist on Cardiac Surgery?

852
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:41,432
I want to become

853
00:31:41,432 --> 00:31:42,433
someone like Dr. Lin.

854
00:31:42,867 --> 00:31:43,768
To save many, many lives

855
00:31:43,768 --> 00:31:45,036
with my own hands.

856
00:31:46,471 --> 00:31:47,038
But right now,

857
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:47,905
I can't even do

858
00:31:47,905 --> 00:31:48,573
the most basic things well.

859
00:31:50,074 --> 00:31:50,808
Honestly, I feel

860
00:31:50,808 --> 00:31:51,609
really stupid.

861
00:31:53,444 --> 00:31:55,446
You... don't say that.

862
00:31:58,116 --> 00:31:59,117
You two are here.

863
00:31:59,150 --> 00:31:59,751
Dr. Fang.

864
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:00,251
Dr. Fang.

865
00:32:00,385 --> 00:32:00,919
Xiao Du.

866
00:32:00,952 --> 00:32:01,986
Come see me when you're done.

867
00:32:02,453 --> 00:32:02,754
Okay.

868
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:11,396
Go on.

869
00:32:12,397 --> 00:32:12,964
I'll help you.

870
00:32:14,065 --> 00:32:15,133
Okay. Thank you.

871
00:32:24,008 --> 00:32:24,909
Dr. Lin

872
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:25,677
asked me to give you this.

873
00:32:25,843 --> 00:32:27,011
It's the practice kit

874
00:32:27,011 --> 00:32:27,712
he used when he was a resident.

875
00:32:28,413 --> 00:32:29,314
Take it and practice.

876
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:34,285
Dr. Lin gave this to me?

877
00:32:34,719 --> 00:32:35,186
Yes.

878
00:32:36,688 --> 00:32:38,256
Don't let him discourage you.

879
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:39,958
He's sharp-tongued

880
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:41,592
but soft-hearted.

881
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:43,361
Technique often comes down

882
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:44,362
to practice.

883
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:45,763
Keep working at it.

884
00:32:46,931 --> 00:32:48,032
But I feel like I'll never

885
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:48,967
reach Dr. Lin's level.

886
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:49,767
Right now, I can't even

887
00:32:50,635 --> 00:32:51,836
do a second assistant's job properly.

888
00:32:51,836 --> 00:32:52,670
Maybe I truly

889
00:32:54,072 --> 00:32:54,839
don't have the talent for this.

890
00:32:54,872 --> 00:32:56,274
What you're doing now

891
00:32:57,108 --> 00:32:58,810
hasn't reached the point

892
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:00,678
where talent decides it.

893
00:33:01,112 --> 00:33:02,046
Becoming

894
00:33:02,046 --> 00:33:03,081
a competent surgeon

895
00:33:03,081 --> 00:33:04,248
is still absolutely possible.

896
00:33:04,682 --> 00:33:05,783
Learn to walk first.

897
00:33:05,983 --> 00:33:06,985
Don't rush to run.

898
00:33:07,585 --> 00:33:08,052
Look.

899
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,388
His stitches back then

900
00:33:10,555 --> 00:33:11,322
were crooked

901
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:12,290
and messy too.

902
00:33:17,895 --> 00:33:20,164
You think he was naturally gifted,

903
00:33:20,431 --> 00:33:21,399
but in truth,

904
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:22,834
he worked far harder

905
00:33:22,867 --> 00:33:23,968
than most people in private.

906
00:33:43,921 --> 00:33:45,323
The hospital's research center

907
00:33:45,556 --> 00:33:47,025
holds regular training.

908
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:48,192
Follow

909
00:33:48,192 --> 00:33:49,093
their official account.

910
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:50,161
Go whenever you have time.

911
00:33:50,895 --> 00:33:52,797
The models and teaching tools

912
00:33:53,131 --> 00:33:54,665
in the training room

913
00:33:54,866 --> 00:33:56,234
are open to hospital doctors.

914
00:33:56,768 --> 00:33:58,302
You only need to book in advance.

915
00:33:58,403 --> 00:33:59,570
The hospital intranet

916
00:33:59,771 --> 00:34:00,571
and Dongjiang Medical College website

917
00:34:00,605 --> 00:34:01,706
also have plenty of

918
00:34:02,273 --> 00:34:03,674
related teaching videos.

919
00:34:04,008 --> 00:34:05,076
Study more. Watch more.

920
00:34:05,910 --> 00:34:06,344
It will definitely help.

921
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:08,513
Okay.

922
00:34:11,516 --> 00:34:12,083
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

923
00:34:12,917 --> 00:34:13,785
And

924
00:34:14,852 --> 00:34:16,187
You're welcome. Keep it up.

925
00:34:16,354 --> 00:34:17,388
You can definitely do it.

926
00:34:30,835 --> 00:34:31,602
Little lady's tresses,

927
00:34:31,769 --> 00:34:32,670
you have to hold on.

928
00:34:33,171 --> 00:34:33,838
In a few days,

929
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:35,006
whether I can show off

930
00:34:35,006 --> 00:34:35,706
in front of my dad

931
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:36,574
depends on you.

932
00:34:37,708 --> 00:34:38,876
Is this thing still alive?

933
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:40,311
It doesn't look like it'll last long.

934
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:41,679
What do you mean?

935
00:34:42,113 --> 00:34:43,047
This is lady's tresses,

936
00:34:43,548 --> 00:34:44,916
one of the smallest orchids.

937
00:34:45,683 --> 00:34:46,517
Its flowering period is short.

938
00:34:46,717 --> 00:34:48,686
Once the blooms reach the top, the season is over.

939
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,154
That's why the flowers are precious.

940
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:52,023
Its flower meaning is cherish the present

941
00:34:52,390 --> 00:34:53,691
and remember it in your heart.

942
00:34:58,663 --> 00:34:59,430
You're just like your dad.

943
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:00,932
The moment you see flowers and plants,

944
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:02,266
you talk nonstop.

945
00:35:03,468 --> 00:35:04,502
I'm telling you something important.

946
00:35:05,169 --> 00:35:06,404
I have three surgeries today,

947
00:35:06,504 --> 00:35:07,705
so I'll definitely be home late.

948
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:09,440
I prepared food for you

949
00:35:09,574 --> 00:35:10,241
and put it in the fridge.

950
00:35:10,475 --> 00:35:11,209
If you want to eat,

951
00:35:11,209 --> 00:35:12,510
just microwave it.

952
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:13,711
There's rice too.

953
00:35:14,011 --> 00:35:14,879
It's in the rice cooker,

954
00:35:15,112 --> 00:35:16,414
already set on timer mode.

955
00:35:16,747 --> 00:35:18,115
Got it.

956
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,051
You don't get anything.

957
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:22,753
Look.

958
00:35:23,588 --> 00:35:24,522
Remember to nap.

959
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:25,823
Rain is forecast today,

960
00:35:25,823 --> 00:35:26,557
so don't go out.

961
00:35:26,691 --> 00:35:28,092
Got it, nag.

962
00:35:28,526 --> 00:35:29,760
Bye-bye.

963
00:35:33,531 --> 00:35:35,133
You can't even say goodbye properly.

964
00:35:45,243 --> 00:35:46,277
The valve is perfectly positioned.

965
00:35:46,477 --> 00:35:47,078
No regurgitation.

966
00:35:48,946 --> 00:35:49,714
The rest is yours.

967
00:35:57,588 --> 00:35:59,090
Director Lin was incredible.

968
00:35:59,490 --> 00:35:59,891
Your TAVR technique

969
00:35:59,891 --> 00:36:00,825
is getting smoother and smoother.

970
00:36:00,958 --> 00:36:02,293
You solved it in seconds.

971
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:04,395
Isn't Boss Lin

972
00:36:04,428 --> 00:36:05,630
always like that?

973
00:36:05,763 --> 00:36:06,631
No learning curve.

974
00:36:06,764 --> 00:36:07,532
Straight to mastery.

975
00:36:08,766 --> 00:36:09,267
Recently,

976
00:36:09,467 --> 00:36:10,401
more and more valve patients

977
00:36:10,601 --> 00:36:11,636
have been booking with our boss.

978
00:36:11,636 --> 00:36:12,470
It scared me into cramming

979
00:36:12,703 --> 00:36:14,272
all weekend.

980
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:15,239
You should study too.

981
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:16,407
You too.

982
00:36:16,407 --> 00:36:17,041
Me too.

983
00:36:18,876 --> 00:36:19,610
Aren't we taking

984
00:36:19,677 --> 00:36:20,545
Cardiology's business?

985
00:36:20,611 --> 00:36:21,646
They haven't complained.

986
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:23,014
Exactly.

987
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:25,416
But what will Director Zhou think?

988
00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:27,451
Director Lin knows what he's doing.

989
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:52,143
Director Lin.

990
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,110
Xu Junsheng's family

991
00:36:53,144 --> 00:36:54,078
is waiting in the office.

992
00:36:54,879 --> 00:36:55,279
All right.

993
00:36:57,415 --> 00:36:57,715
Let's go.

994
00:36:57,815 --> 00:36:58,115
Let's go.

995
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,851
We finally get to see you, Director Lin.

996
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:35,386
What's wrong?

997
00:37:35,853 --> 00:37:36,587
Nothing at all.

998
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:37,855
Thanks to you,

999
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:39,390
he recovered extremely well.

1000
00:37:39,724 --> 00:37:40,324
We came today

1001
00:37:40,891 --> 00:37:42,293
especially to thank you.

1002
00:37:42,493 --> 00:37:43,928
Yes, Director Lin.

1003
00:37:44,362 --> 00:37:45,730
Thank you for saving his life.

1004
00:37:46,597 --> 00:37:47,665
Yes, Director Lin.

1005
00:37:48,132 --> 00:37:49,166
And this.

1006
00:37:49,367 --> 00:37:49,800
Yes.

1007
00:37:50,401 --> 00:37:51,836
You saved our whole family

1008
00:37:52,036 --> 00:37:53,371
and brought our father back to life.

1009
00:37:54,672 --> 00:37:55,439
That's the most down-to-earth

1010
00:37:55,473 --> 00:37:56,907
banner slogan I've ever seen.

1011
00:37:57,041 --> 00:37:58,209
It's from the heart.

1012
00:37:58,376 --> 00:37:59,210
Yes, yes. From the heart.

1013
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:00,311
Director Lin, come on.

1014
00:38:00,311 --> 00:38:01,245
Let's take a photo.

1015
00:38:01,245 --> 00:38:02,747
Yes, yes. A photo.

1016
00:38:02,747 --> 00:38:03,147
Come, come.

1017
00:38:03,214 --> 00:38:03,914
I'll take it for you.

1018
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:04,282
Okay.

1019
00:38:04,348 --> 00:38:05,249
Director Lin accepts everyone's kindness.

1020
00:38:05,249 --> 00:38:05,650
Come on.

1021
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:07,051
Director Lin, look here.

1022
00:38:07,451 --> 00:38:09,287
Three, two, one.

1023
00:38:51,295 --> 00:38:52,196
He hasn't eaten anything.

1024
00:39:23,427 --> 00:39:23,961
Xiaorui.

1025
00:39:24,662 --> 00:39:25,229
Xiaorui.

1026
00:39:26,163 --> 00:39:26,630
Xiaorui.

1027
00:39:27,732 --> 00:39:28,265
Xiaorui.

1028
00:39:39,076 --> 00:39:39,543
Ventricular fibrillation.

1029
00:39:39,643 --> 00:39:40,444
Start defibrillation.

1030
00:39:40,811 --> 00:39:41,645
Does he have a pacemaker?

1031
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:43,681
Yes.

1032
00:39:44,482 --> 00:39:45,483
It was just implanted recently.

1033
00:39:45,483 --> 00:39:46,250
A CRT pacemaker with defibrillation.

1034
00:39:46,283 --> 00:39:47,151
With heart failure this severe,

1035
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:47,918
the myocardium probably

1036
00:39:47,952 --> 00:39:48,753
has almost no contractility left.

1037
00:39:48,919 --> 00:39:49,887
The pacemaker isn't working.

1038
00:39:50,988 --> 00:39:51,589
Charge complete.

1039
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:52,623
Clear.

1040
00:40:10,207 --> 00:40:10,875
Family, step back.

1041
00:40:11,008 --> 00:40:12,376
Send the patient directly

1042
00:40:21,152 --> 00:40:21,952
Make way. Make way.

1043
00:40:22,153 --> 00:40:23,454
Move aside. Hurry.

1044
00:42:02,887 --> 00:42:03,754
Prepare to defibrillate.

1045
00:42:28,078 --> 00:42:28,812
Continue compressions.

1046
00:42:46,830 --> 00:42:47,831
He needs ECMO.

1047
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:49,567
Director.

1048
00:42:52,369 --> 00:42:53,971
Severe heart failure with recurrent VF.

1049
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:55,272
We have to initiate

1050
00:42:55,272 --> 00:42:55,606
ECMO now.

1051
00:42:55,606 --> 00:42:56,507
You're his legal guardian.

1052
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:57,241
Do you consent?
